  "local_port": 56180,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What universities does Inteliquent recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Inteliquent, a leading provider of telecommunications services, recruits new graduates from a variety of universities across the United States and possibly internationally. While specific recruiting partners can vary over time based on company needs and strategic initiatives, Inteliquent typically targets institutions known for strong programs in areas relevant to their business. Some of the universities they may recruit from include:\n\n### **Potential Universities for Recruitment:**\n- **Major Research Universities:**\n  - **Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)**\n  - **Stanford University**\n  - **University of California, Berkeley**\n  - **Carnegie Mellon University**\n  - **Georgia Institute of Technology**\n  \n- **State Universities:**\n  - **University of Texas at Austin**\n  - **University of Michigan**\n  - **University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign**\n  - **Purdue University**\n  - **Pennsylvania State University**\n\n- **Regional Universities and Colleges:**\n  - **Northeastern University**\n  - **University of Denver**\n  - **Rochester Institute of Technology**\n  - **Oregon State University**\n  - **Virginia Tech**\n\n### **Desired Majors and Disciplines:**\nInteliquent seeks candidates with diverse academic backgrounds that align with their operations and strategic goals. Key majors and disciplines they often look for include:\n\n- **Computer Science & Information Technology:**\n  - Software Engineering\n  - Network Engineering\n  - Cybersecurity\n  - Data Science\n\n- **Engineering:**\n  - Electrical Engineering\n  - Telecommunications Engineering\n  - Systems Engineering\n\n- **Business & Finance:**\n  - Business Administration\n  - Marketing\n  - Finance\n  - Supply Chain Management\n\n- **Sales & Marketing:**\n  - Communications\n  - Marketing\n  - Public Relations\n\n- **Other Relevant Fields:**\n  - Mathematics and Statistics\n  - Project Management\n  - Information Systems\n\n### **Additional Considerations:**\n- **Internship Experience:** Having relevant internship experience can significantly enhance a candidate's prospects.\n- **Technical Skills:** Proficiency in programming languages, data analysis tools, and other technical skills pertinent to the role.\n- **Soft Skills:** Strong communication, teamwork, problem-solving abilities, and adaptability are highly valued.\n- **Certifications:** Relevant certifications (e.g., Cisco, CompTIA) can be advantageous, especially for technical roles.\n\n### **How to Learn More:**\n- **Careers Page:** Visit Inteliquent\u2019s official [Careers](https://www.inteliquent.com/careers/) page to find current job postings, internship opportunities, and specific recruiting events.\n- **University Recruitment Events:** Attend career fairs and on-campus recruiting events where Inteliquent may be present.\n- **LinkedIn:** Follow Inteliquent on [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/inteliquent/) to stay updated on job openings and company news.\n- **Networking:** Connect with current employees or alumni from your university who work at Inteliquent for insights and potential referrals.\n\n### **Final Tips:**\n- **Tailor Your Application:** Ensure your resume and cover letter highlight relevant skills and experiences that match the job description.\n- **Prepare for Interviews:** Be ready to discuss your technical skills, project experiences, and how you can contribute to Inteliquent\u2019s goals.\n- **Stay Informed:** Keep abreast of the latest trends and developments in the telecommunications industry to demonstrate your enthusiasm and knowledge during the recruitment process.\n\nBy targeting universities with strong programs in relevant fields and seeking candidates with a mix of technical and soft skills, Inteliquent aims to build a talented and versatile workforce to support its role in the telecommunications industry.",
